Overall Survival (Months): Overall survival in months since initial diagonosis.
Patient's Vital Status: The survival state of the person.
Primary Tumor Laterality: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the cancer originates.
Tumor Other Histologic Subtype: Text to describe a tumor's histologic subtype or mixed diagnosis that is different from previously specified options.
Relapse Free Status: Relapse Free Status (Recurred = cases where there was loco-regional relapse, distant relapse or death-specific death)
Relapse Free Status (Months): Time until last follow-up or relapse (in months)
